<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-502-003  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 502 003.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 9 1990 v4 n34 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Stacks ease language translation. (D'Agostini Organizzazione'sHyperTrans software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenthal, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   D'Agostini Organizzazione (product introduction).andO;Product:   HyperTRANS (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionLanguage TranslationSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Steve RosenthalandM;Paris -- Professional language translators attending Apple Expo here latelast month saw a new HyperCard-based system that lets them produce roughdrafts or check words or phrases.andM;Created by D'Agostini Organizzazione, an Italian developer, HyperTrans usesboth look-up tables and contextual rules to provide word equivalentsappropriate to the subject being translated and surrounding material.andM;The program, said author Giovanni D'Agostini, is the result of a cooperativeventure between the company and customers.andP;  Users first send a typical set ofdocuments to D'Agostini's offices in Udine, Italy.andP;  His company then developsan initial set of custom rules for that user's context.andP;  After receiving theprogram, the user continues to send monthly reports of inaccuracies to thepublisher, who continues to modify the rule set and issue new versions.andM;D'Agostini Organizzazione has already produced or is working on languagepairs for most major European languages.andP;  U.S.andP;  orders are supported fromItaly.andM;Typical prices range from $4,274 for Italian/English to $20,513 forEnglish/German translation software.andM;D'Agostini Organizzazione is located at Via G. Giusti No.andP;  17, 33100 Udine,Italy; 432-507332.andO;</TEXT></DOC>